You can if you want, but you don't *need* to. 23 lb-ft on a VW head bolt
(are those Grade 8 bolts?) isn't going to kill the threads. Now, on a 350
Chevrolet or a Detroit Diesel 6V71, where you apply some serious amounts of
torque, that's a different story.
